Apigee Corporation: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 9:27 AM ET
Internet Software and Services

Company Overview of Apigee Corporation



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Apigee Corporation develops a software platform that enables API-based digital strategies and business insights for enterprises. Its platform allows businesses to design, deploy, and scale APIs as a connection layer between information technology systems and data, and the applications with which its customers, partners, employees, and other users engage with the business. The company’s platform includes Apigee Edge, a self-service API platform for businesses to manage the digital value chain; Apigee Edge PRO, an API management for small and medium-sized businesses, and divisions in large enterprises; and Apigee Sense, a bot prevention product that leverages sophisticated machine learning alg...
Apigee Corporation develops a software platform that enables API-based digital strategies and business insights for enterprises. Its platform allows businesses to design, deploy, and scale APIs as a connection layer between information technology systems and data, and the applications with which its customers, partners, employees, and other users engage with the business. The company’s platform includes Apigee Edge, a self-service API platform for businesses to manage the digital value chain; Apigee Edge PRO, an API management for small and medium-sized businesses, and divisions in large enterprises; and Apigee Sense, a bot prevention product that leverages sophisticated machine learning algorithms to detect bad bots at the API layer. Its platform also comprise Apigee Insights, a self-service predictive analytics solution for enterprises to find time-based patterns in big data and gain insights to provide personalized experiences, enhance customer satisfaction and retention, and grow revenue and profits; and Apigee Link, an Internet of Things platform for connecting devices to the Internet. In addition, the company provides professional services, including consulting, training, configuration, and implementation services; maintenance and customer support services; and classroom and virtual classroom, and on-demand training. It serves customers in various industry segments, such as telecommunications, media and entertainment, financial services, retail, travel and hospitality, and healthcare and insurance. The company offers its products through direct field sales, direct inside sales, and indirect channel sales in the United States, the United Kingdom, and internationally. The company was formerly known as Sonoa Systems, Inc. and changed its name to Apigee Corporation in September 2010. The company was founded in 2004 and is headquartered in San Jose, California. As of November 10, 2016, Apigee Corporation operates as a subsidiary of Google Inc.
Detailed Description


